---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

const post = {
 title: 'Custom Polo Shirts: Embroidery, Fabric, and Vendor Selection Guide',
 description:
 'Custom polos with an embroidered logo are the default for service techs, account managers, and customer-facing roles. Here\'s how to pick the right blank — Port Authority, Carhartt, Nike, Cutter & Buck — and what to ask before you order.',
 category: 'Products',
 readTime: '9 min read',
 date: 'May 9, 2026',
 isoDate: '2026-05-09',
 image: '/images/generated/service-embroidery.jpg',
 slug: 'custom-polo-shirts-las-vegas',
}

const faqs = [
 { q: 'What\'s the best blank polo for a custom embroidered company shirt?', a: 'Port Authority K500 Silk Touch is the workhorse — pique cotton-poly, holds embroidery cleanly, available in 30+ colors S–6XL, comparable price across all sizes. For higher-end brands, Cutter & Buck DryTec, Nike Dri-FIT, and Travis Mathew performance polos cost 2-3x more but feel and look premium. Carhartt Workwear Pocket Polo is the trade-friendly pick.' },
 { q: 'Should custom polo shirts be embroidered or screen printed?', a: 'Embroidery — almost always. The premium look of stitched thread on a pique knit polo reads as "established business" the way a screen-printed polo never does. Screen printing on polos is reserved for high-volume promotional runs where cost is the priority over feel. Embroidery is the standard for any client-facing role.' },
 { q: 'How much should custom polos cost?', a: 'Per-piece cost depends on the blank, the embroidery stitch count, and the order quantity. Port Authority K500 with a left-chest logo at 24 pieces typically runs $25-40 each including embroidery and digitizing. Premium blanks (Nike Dri-FIT, Travis Mathew) push that to $50-75. Bulk discounts kick in at 48 pieces and again at 144+.' },
 { q: 'Can you embroider names on every polo without slowing the order down?', a: 'Yes. Once digitizing is done, name embroidery adds about a day to the standard run — not a week. We stitch each name to order; per-shirt cost is fixed regardless of name length. Worth doing for service techs and customer-facing staff where the name on the chest is the trust signal.' },
 { q: 'What fabric should custom polos be in for Las Vegas summer?', a: 'Moisture-wicking polyester or poly-blend. Port Authority K540 Silk Touch Performance Polo and Sport-Tek ST650 are the two most-ordered for Vegas summer service work — they wick sweat, dry fast, and don\'t soak through by 11am the way 100% cotton polos do. Cotton looks nicer at week one but loses by July.' },
 { q: 'What\'s the minimum order for custom embroidered polos?', a: 'Most shops set 12-24 pieces as the practical minimum. Below that, per-piece pricing climbs because digitizing and setup is amortized over fewer shirts. For very small orders (4-12 pieces), expect a higher per-piece price or a small order surcharge.' },
 { q: 'Where can I get custom polo shirts in Las Vegas?', a: 'Bighorn Threads runs custom embroidered polos for Vegas contractors, service businesses, and trade companies. We stock Port Authority, Sport-Tek, Carhartt, and Nike polos in standard sizes S-4XL with embroidery turned around quickly when artwork is ready. Get a quote with your logo and quantity.' },
]

const schema = {
 '@context': 'https://schema.org',
 '@graph': [
 { '@type': 'Article', headline: post.title, description: post.description, image: `https://bighornthreads.com${post.image}`, datePublished: post.isoDate, dateModified: post.isoDate, author: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'Bighorn Threads', url: 'https://bighornthreads.com/' }, publisher: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'Bighorn Threads', logo: { '@type': 'ImageObject', url: 'https://bighornthreads.com/images/logos/bighorn-logo-color.png' } }, mainEntityOfPage: `https://bighornthreads.com/blog/${post.slug}/` },
 { '@type': 'BreadcrumbList', itemListElement: [{ '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: 'https://bighornthreads.com/' }, { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Blog', item: 'https://bighornthreads.com/blog/' }, { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 3, name: post.title, item: `https://bighornthreads.com/blog/${post.slug}/` }] },
 { '@type': 'FAQPage', mainEntity: faqs.map((f) => ({ '@type': 'Question', name: f.q, acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: f.a } })) },
 ],
}
---

<BaseLayout title={post.title} description={post.description} canonical={`https://bighornthreads.com/blog/${post.slug}/`} ogImage={post.image} type="article" publishedDate={post.isoDate}>
 <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />
 <article class="bg-concrete">
 <header class="border-b border-hairline bg-paper">
 <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 pt-20 pb-12 sm:px-6 sm:pt-24 lg:px-8">
 <nav class="mb-6 font-mono text-xs text-ash" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/" class="hover:text-gold-700">Home</a><span class="px-2">/</span><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-gold-700">Blog</a></nav>
 <span class="mb-3 inline-block text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-gold-600">{post.category}</span>
 <h1 class="mb-6 font-heading text-3xl font-bold leading-tight tracking-tight sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl">{post.title}</h1>
 <p class="mb-8 text-xl leading-relaxed text-ash">A working buyer's guide to custom embroidered polos — what blank to pick, how the embroidery affects the price, and what to ask before you order.</p>
 <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-4 gap-y-2 border-t border-hairline pt-6 font-mono text-sm text-ash"><span class="text-gold-600">Bighorn Threads Team</span><span aria-hidden="true">&middot;</span><span>{post.readTime}</span><span aria-hidden="true">&middot;</span><time datetime={post.isoDate}>{post.date}</time></div>
 </div>
 </header>
 <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 pt-10 sm:px-6 lg:px-8"><img src={post.image} alt="Embroidered Port Authority K500 silk touch polo with company logo on left chest" width="1200" height="675" loading="eager" class="w-full border border-hairline object-cover" /></div>
 <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

 <aside class="mb-10 border border-hairline bg-panel p-7">
 <p class="mb-3 font-mono text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-gold-600">Quick Answer</p>
 <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-charcoal sm:text-xl">Custom polo shirts with an embroidered chest logo are the default for service techs, account managers, sales reps, and customer-facing staff. Port Authority K500 Silk Touch is the workhorse blank ($15-22 wholesale, embroiders cleanly, 30+ colors). For Vegas summer service work, swap to the K540 Performance moisture-wicking version. Premium brands (Nike Dri-FIT, Travis Mathew, Cutter & Buck) cost 2-3x more and read as such.</p>
 </aside>

 <h2 id="when-polo" class="mt-12 mb-4 font-heading text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">When to Use a Custom Polo</h2>
 <p class="mb-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-charcoal">Polos are the right pick for any role where employees are seen by customers, vendors, or the public — and the visual signal needs to read as "professional, established business," not "team event." See our <a href="/custom-polo-shirts-las-vegas/" class="text-gold-600 underline decoration-gold-600/40 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-gold-600">custom polo shirts Las Vegas</a> page for brand options and current blank inventory.</p>
 <p class="mb-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-charcoal">For trades and service businesses, that means:</p>
 <ul class="mb-6 list-disc pl-6 space-y-3 text-lg leading-relaxed text-charcoal">
 <li>Service technicians at a residential or commercial customer's location</li>
 <li>Account managers and sales reps in client meetings</li>
 <li>Estimators on site walkthroughs</li>
 <li>Office staff and dispatchers in the front-of-house</li>
 <li>Foremen and supervisors when a visual cue separates them from field crew</li>
 </ul>
 <p class="mb-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-charcoal">Field crews working in dirty, abrasive conditions (concrete, masonry, demo) usually skip polos and run on heavyweight tees instead — see <a href="/blog/how-to-outfit-a-construction-crew-vegas/" class="text-gold-600 underline decoration-gold-600/40 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-gold-600">how to outfit a construction crew</a>.</p>

 <h2 id="blanks" class="mt-12 mb-4 font-heading text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">The Polo Blanks That Matter</h2>

 <h3 class="mt-8 mb-3 font-heading text-xl font-bold">Port Authority K500 Silk Touch — the workhorse</h3>
 <p class="mb-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-charcoal">If you've seen a generic embroidered company polo in the last decade, it was probably a Port Authority K500. Pique knit cotton-poly blend, available in 30+ colors, S-6XL, holds embroidery cleanly, comparable price across the size range. The default pick for service businesses, contractors, and trade crews.</p>

 <h3 class="mt-8 mb-3 font-heading text-xl font-bold">Port Authority K540 Performance — for Vegas heat</h3>
 <p class="mb-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-charcoal">Same cut and embroidery profile as the K500 but with moisture-wicking polyester. The right swap for Vegas summer where service techs are working through 110° conditions. Same per-piece price as the K500. There is no good reason to spec a 100% cotton polo for a Vegas service crew operating June through September.</p>

 <h3 class="mt-8 mb-3 font-heading text-xl font-bold">Carhartt Workwear Pocket Polo — trade-friendly</h3>
 <p class="mb-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-charcoal">Heavier-weight polo with a chest pocket. Reads as a trade-friendly piece — fits naturally on a contractor or service tech without looking like office attire. Slightly higher per-piece cost than the K500 but the chest pocket is functional for pens, badges, and small tools.</p>

 <h3 class="mt-8 mb-3 font-heading text-xl font-bold">Nike Dri-FIT, Travis Mathew, Cutter & Buck — premium</h3>
 <p class="mb-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-charcoal">For client-facing executive roles, business development, and ownership. These polos cost $40-75 wholesale (vs. $15-22 for Port Authority) but the difference is visible at a glance. The right call when the polo is going on a person whose attire signals authority — at industry events, in client meetings, on speaking engagements. Embroidery placement and stitch density work the same way as on the workhorse blanks.</p>

 <h2 id="embroidery" class="mt-12 mb-4 font-heading text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Embroidery on Polos</h2>
 <p class="mb-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-charcoal">A standard left-chest polo logo runs 5,000-8,000 stitches at 3-3.5 inches wide. Larger logos can push 12,000+ stitches but get visually heavy on a knit fabric — the embroidery starts to look distorted on stretchy pique. Smaller logos (under 2 inches) lose detail because the stitch count to maintain legibility doesn't fit in the available area.</p>
 <p class="mb-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-charcoal">Optional placements:</p>
 <ul class="mb-6 list-disc pl-6 space-y-3 text-lg leading-relaxed text-charcoal">
 <li><strong>Right chest:</strong> Employee name. Standard for service techs.</li>
 <li><strong>Sleeve:</strong> Department, certification badge, or secondary mark.</li>
 <li><strong>Back yoke:</strong> License number, service line phone number, or company URL. Less common on polos than on work shirts.</li>
 </ul>
 <p class="mb-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-charcoal">For full pricing context, see <a href="/blog/how-much-to-embroider-a-shirt/" class="text-gold-600 underline decoration-gold-600/40 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-gold-600">how much it costs to embroider a shirt</a>.</p>

 <h2 id="vegas" class="mt-12 mb-4 font-heading text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Vegas-Specific Polo Picks by Industry</h2>
 <ul class="mb-6 list-disc pl-6 space-y-3 text-lg leading-relaxed text-charcoal">
 <li><strong>Service trades</strong> (<a href="/industries/plumbing-hvac-las-vegas/" class="text-gold-600 underline decoration-gold-600/40 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-gold-600">plumbing, HVAC</a>, <a href="/industries/electrical-contractors-las-vegas/" class="text-gold-600 underline decoration-gold-600/40 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-gold-600">electrical</a>): Port Authority K540 Performance with embroidered logo + name. The summer-friendly default.</li>
 <li><strong>Office and account managers</strong>: Port Authority K500 in colors that match the brand palette.</li>
 <li><strong>Roofing and solar</strong> (<a href="/industries/roofing-solar-las-vegas/" class="text-gold-600 underline decoration-gold-600/40 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-gold-600">crew</a>): Skip polos for the install crew, run them only on supervisors and account managers.</li>
 <li><strong>Real estate, lending, professional services</strong>: Premium blanks (Nike Dri-FIT, Travis Mathew) for ownership and client-facing roles; Port Authority for support staff.</li>
 </ul>

 <h2 id="ordering" class="mt-12 mb-4 font-heading text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">How to Order Custom Polos</h2>
 <ol class="mb-6 list-decimal pl-6 space-y-3 text-lg leading-relaxed text-charcoal">
 <li><strong>Pick your blank.</strong> Default to Port Authority K500/K540 unless brand identity calls for premium.</li>
 <li><strong>Send your logo.</strong> Vector format (.ai, .eps) is best.</li>
 <li><strong>Specify quantity + sizing.</strong> Most polo programs run 5 polos per employee per season as the baseline.</li>
 <li><strong>Decide on names.</strong> Service techs and customer-facing roles benefit from name embroidery; office staff usually don't need it.</li>
 <li><strong>Pick placements.</strong> Left chest is standard; add sleeve or right-chest name if it fits the program.</li>
 </ol>

 <div class="mt-12 border border-hairline bg-gold-500/5 p-7 sm:p-9">
 <h2 class="mb-3 font-heading text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-charcoal">Custom embroidered polos in Las Vegas</h2>
 <p class="mb-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-charcoal">Bighorn Threads runs custom embroidered polos for Vegas contractors, trade businesses, and service companies. Send your logo and crew sizes — we'll quote per piece including digitizing.</p>
 <a href="/contact/" class="inline-flex min-h-[48px] items-center gap-2 bg-gold-500 px-7 py-3 text-base font-bold text-charcoal transition-all hover:bg-gold-600">Get a Quote →</a>
 </div>
 </div>
 </article>
</BaseLayout>
